    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasRequirement": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/req/fda-guidance-fea-spinal-2021",
    "type": "Requirement",
    "name": "FDA Guidance: Reporting of Computational Modeling Studies in Medical Device Submissions (2021)",
    "description": "The FEA submission must demonstrate model credibility commensurate with the risk level of the device and the influence of the model on the regulatory decision. For Class II spinal implants under ASTM F1717, computational predictions of construct stiffness, yield force, and displacement-at-failure must be validated against physical bench testing with quantified agreement metrics and uncertainty characterization.",
    "source": "https://www.fda.gov/regulatory-information/search-fda-guidance-documents/assessing-credibility-computational-modeling-through-verification-and-validation-application-medical"
